text: For fuck sake people, it's a trailer! You can't judge the movie by the trailer!    "Bad acting, bad writing," the trailer isn't meant to be a grade A English assignment, it's to show what the movie is about, the plot, the elements - and so on. I hated the look of Gravity, I thought it'd be amazingly stupid, a survival movie out in space . . . How boring. But it turned out to be one of my favourite movies and I was stupid to judge it by the trailer! And "I just saw the whole movie in the trailer," I swear there is one of those idiots on every trailer! What'd this trailer show that was the whole movie? The main characters, the plot and why they are there, destruction, and tornados. Well fuck me, that's the whole movie there, isn't it? I mean we haven't seen the beginning, middle, or end, but hey, the trailer has a lot of booms and screams so lets just assume it's the whole movie.     This type of survival, storm movies might not be for you. Cool, great! Go jerk off to the latest Transformers trailer then. I'm sure two robotic aliens fighting will suffice your needs for a good movie! - and yes it's sarcasm, Transformers is terrible.       And copy of Twister? OK, I loved Twister. I grew up watching it whenever I could. But many, and I mean many movies have had tornados in them. There not copying Twister. And if your simple minds wrapped around the plot of Twister - it's a group of scientists/tornado chasers trying to create an early warning system for tornados. This just looks like tornado chasers and a scientist got caught up in the wrong place at the wrong time!     Not to go all terms on people but it's no longer called "F5" tornados, it's been renamed to "EF 1,2,3,4,5" tornados . . .

Especially with the popularity of Storm Chasers and Tornado Chasers, and the horrifying tornadoes not only this year but in 2013 that killed many including chasers featured in the TV show Storm Chasers (el Reno tornado May 31,2013). For those affected by those terrible storms, this film might be too traumatic to watch.

It was 2.6 miles wide and it had wind speeds of over 296 mph. It was wider than Manhatten and central park in new york. However,  there was a tornado on June 16, 1928  that was reported to be 7 miles wide in blair, oklahoma.  This movie takes place in oklahoma. Oklahoma has big tornadoes. Huge!!  This movie is very well written.  People are going about their regular schedules and have to change their plans just like I had to do in real life. Five tornadoes went through okc following the el reno tornado on may 31, 2013. The highest wind speed ever recorded on earth was located 23 miles from el reno. It was in bridge creek, Oklahoma.
